WEBVTT

00:07.563 --> 00:10.396
(projector whirs)

00:55.670 --> 00:57.750
- I should've never let you in here.

00:57.750 --> 01:00.233
- You shouldn't have gotten
mixed in with those guys.

01:02.010 --> 01:03.283
What are you afraid of?

01:14.409 --> 01:16.379
(gun fires)
(Fay grunts)

01:16.379 --> 01:19.629
(serene country music)

03:06.770 --> 03:08.930
- Why'd you leave so early?

03:08.930 --> 03:10.523
I wanted to make you breakfast.

03:11.990 --> 03:15.763
Yeah, I know, I'll be able to
make you breakfast every day.

03:18.460 --> 03:21.453
Yeah, no, me, I gotta go
pick up my assignment.

03:22.390 --> 03:25.190
I'm not sure yet, but
I'm hoping it's not far.

03:25.190 --> 03:28.513
You know, L.A. traffic
is already a nightmare.

03:30.980 --> 03:33.313
Okay, babe, I'll see you tonight?

03:34.970 --> 03:35.803
Love you too.

03:37.653 --> 03:38.704
Bye.

03:47.661 --> 03:50.244
(somber music)

04:54.079 --> 04:57.246
(radio static buzzes)

05:03.733 --> 05:06.882
- [Anchor] The country is in
a complete civil race war.

05:06.882 --> 05:10.019
(police sirens wail)
(guns fire)

05:10.019 --> 05:12.220
- Is someone shooting?

05:12.220 --> 05:13.362
(gun fires)
(Fay screams)

05:13.362 --> 05:17.200
God, move, move!
(tires screech)

05:17.200 --> 05:19.533
(guns fire)

05:24.566 --> 05:25.421
Not again.
(gun fires)

05:25.421 --> 05:30.004
(Fay yelps)
(crashing)

05:49.389 --> 05:51.889
(tense music)

05:55.584 --> 05:57.917
(men grunt)

06:03.376 --> 06:06.459
(police sirens wail)

06:11.785 --> 06:13.046
Call me back, call me back, I need you!

06:13.046 --> 06:15.940
(man shouts)
I'm downtown near 10th!

06:15.940 --> 06:18.023
(grunts)

06:27.871 --> 06:30.871
(suspenseful music)

06:59.950 --> 07:02.440
(locks click)

07:02.440 --> 07:04.630
Hey, hey.

07:04.630 --> 07:06.200
I hear you, somebody in there?

07:06.200 --> 07:07.033
Somebody?

07:11.138 --> 07:14.555
(helicopter blades whir)

07:25.330 --> 07:26.621
(foreboding music)

07:26.621 --> 07:27.767
(knocking)

07:27.767 --> 07:28.667
- [Man] Yo, bitch!

07:30.080 --> 07:32.457
Yo, bitch, I know you in there!

07:33.580 --> 07:35.150
I hear you!

07:35.150 --> 07:36.350
I'm coming for your ass!

07:38.820 --> 07:40.700
Yeah, we'll be back!

08:31.796 --> 08:34.963
(newscaster chatters)

08:39.710 --> 08:40.933
- What the fuck?

08:42.374 --> 08:47.374
(people shout)
(guns fire)

08:47.534 --> 08:49.670
- [Man] Let's go, cover your head!

08:49.670 --> 08:50.893
- They finally did it.

08:52.260 --> 08:54.520
- Who finally did what?

08:54.520 --> 08:55.670
- This has been coming.

08:56.960 --> 08:59.973
For anybody listening, watching.

09:01.370 --> 09:02.420
This has been coming.

09:04.129 --> 09:08.611
(helicopter blades whir)
(woman screams)

09:08.611 --> 09:10.944
(gun fires)

09:17.023 --> 09:18.560
- I have to see what's going on.

09:18.560 --> 09:19.790
My car is out there.

09:19.790 --> 09:21.660
- You know what's going on.

09:21.660 --> 09:23.163
You were already out there.

09:24.270 --> 09:25.563
Just getting worse.

09:27.631 --> 09:30.548
(dial tone blares)

09:32.410 --> 09:34.323
- [Fay] Do you have a phone I could use?

09:35.360 --> 09:36.863
- Stopped working an hour ago.

09:39.640 --> 09:42.070
- Well is there another way out of here?

09:42.070 --> 09:43.120
What about that door?

09:44.600 --> 09:45.803
- It's just storage.

09:48.110 --> 09:50.460
This is the safest place
in the city right now.

09:53.010 --> 09:55.490
- [Fay] What are you, some kind of artist?

09:55.490 --> 09:57.660
- Bingo, what gave me away?

09:57.660 --> 09:59.600
All my dirty paintbrushes?

09:59.600 --> 10:01.780
Or my high fashion wardrobe?

10:01.780 --> 10:04.930
- What's a white girl
doing living down here?

10:04.930 --> 10:06.280
You slumming?

10:06.280 --> 10:09.030
- Till my splashes of color
can actually make me money,

10:09.890 --> 10:11.940
warehouse in the hood is
all a white girl can afford.

10:11.940 --> 10:14.164
- We just heard a big explosion.

10:14.164 --> 10:16.000
(guns fire)
Not more than a block

10:16.000 --> 10:17.060
away from us.

10:17.060 --> 10:20.740
And a gang of men, a gang of armed men

10:20.740 --> 10:22.970
have been going back and
forth from each other.

10:22.970 --> 10:25.576
There's been looting everywhere.

10:25.576 --> 10:26.730
(people shout angrily)

10:26.730 --> 10:29.390
This is Fabia Lopez, back
to you at the studio.

10:29.390 --> 10:30.616
Let's get out of here.

10:30.616 --> 10:32.949
(gun fires)

10:33.944 --> 10:35.804
(static buzzes)

10:35.804 --> 10:38.721
(foreboding music)

11:05.641 --> 11:08.558
(car alarm blares)

11:10.470 --> 11:13.370
- Might as well make
ourselves comfortable.

11:13.370 --> 11:15.040
There's not much we can do.

11:15.040 --> 11:16.183
Just ride it out.

11:17.060 --> 11:19.610
- This is not just some
wave that will come and go.

11:20.830 --> 11:22.990
- No, you're right.

11:22.990 --> 11:25.540
Like all waves, there'll
be another one after this.

11:26.600 --> 11:27.950
And another one after that.

11:29.570 --> 11:31.120
- You don't look like a surfer.

11:32.290 --> 11:33.123
- I'm not.

11:34.010 --> 11:36.260
Just a student of history
and human behavior.

11:53.594 --> 11:56.261
(ominous music)

12:01.930 --> 12:03.333
Called some of my friends.

12:04.580 --> 12:05.930
They should be here by now.

12:08.400 --> 12:10.950
- Thought you said the
phone stopped working.

12:10.950 --> 12:11.783
- It did.

12:12.810 --> 12:14.260
I talked to him this morning.

12:16.670 --> 12:18.103
They're coming in from out of town.

12:40.027 --> 12:43.027
(men shout angrily)

12:46.430 --> 12:50.763
(gun fires)
(gasps)

13:00.534 --> 13:03.451
(melancholy music)

13:11.791 --> 13:13.291
- We did it, Pops.

13:18.470 --> 13:19.793
I got my badge today.

13:22.430 --> 13:23.263
Yeah.

13:28.890 --> 13:30.510
I know you always wanted a boy

13:31.840 --> 13:33.733
to follow in the family legacy.

13:36.920 --> 13:38.623
But I guess it was me, huh?

13:44.400 --> 13:49.243
And I promise I'm gonna be
the best cop you ever saw.

13:54.960 --> 13:56.080
(sobs)
- We should stay away

13:56.080 --> 13:57.193
from the windows.

13:58.890 --> 14:00.339
We don't want anyone to see us.

14:00.339 --> 14:01.610
- No.

14:01.610 --> 14:04.610
We can't just sit here and do nothing.

14:04.610 --> 14:06.630
We have to do--
- What?

14:06.630 --> 14:07.740
We have to what?

14:08.750 --> 14:11.190
The world is on fire.

14:11.190 --> 14:13.520
If we go out there, we'll burn with it.

14:13.520 --> 14:15.320
- Well you might be okay with just sitting

14:15.320 --> 14:17.573
and watching it burn, but I'm not.

14:18.450 --> 14:20.193
- There's nothing we can do.

14:22.150 --> 14:25.510
Who do you think you are,
some kind of wonder woman?

14:25.510 --> 14:26.870
- No.

14:26.870 --> 14:29.497
I'm a--
(phone rings)

14:35.660 --> 14:37.623
Ric, where are you?

14:39.580 --> 14:41.670
I'm okay, I'm...

14:41.670 --> 14:42.850
I don't even know what happened.

14:42.850 --> 14:46.023
I was leaving downtown from
work when everything happened.

14:47.410 --> 14:49.460
Yes, yes, I'm safe right now, I'm...

14:51.170 --> 14:53.710
I'm in a warehouse building near Central.

14:53.710 --> 14:54.943
What's the address here?

14:56.020 --> 14:58.170
- There's no address outside.

14:58.170 --> 15:00.770
Just middle of the
block on 14th, red door.

15:00.770 --> 15:03.060
- Middle of the block on 14th, red door.

15:03.060 --> 15:04.160
I'll look out for you.

15:08.790 --> 15:10.350
What's going on?

15:10.350 --> 15:12.710
I can't see anything.

15:12.710 --> 15:14.350
This is crazy.

15:14.350 --> 15:16.020
I mean, they always said
something like this would happen,

15:16.020 --> 15:17.760
but I never thought...

15:24.360 --> 15:27.830
Just be safe and get
here as fast as you can.

15:27.830 --> 15:29.270
Okay?

15:29.270 --> 15:31.820
Okay, I love you.

15:31.820 --> 15:34.364
(dial tone blares)

15:34.364 --> 15:35.197
Fuck.

15:38.700 --> 15:40.550
- I think there's somebody out there.

15:41.432 --> 15:43.000
- What are you talking about?

15:43.000 --> 15:45.563
- I think I see somebody,
but I'm not sure.

15:45.563 --> 15:48.646
(police siren wails)

16:17.260 --> 16:18.310
- It's a little girl.

16:20.090 --> 16:21.143
- Is she alive?

16:22.530 --> 16:23.961
- I don't know.

16:23.961 --> 16:25.190
(helicopter blades whir)

16:25.190 --> 16:26.190
I'm going out there.

16:28.820 --> 16:30.550
Go to the window and look out for me.

16:30.550 --> 16:33.623
If you see something,
you see anyone, yell out.

16:34.600 --> 16:36.050
Can you open the door for me?

16:38.835 --> 16:39.785
I'll be right back.

16:49.450 --> 16:50.283
Hey.

16:54.250 --> 16:55.083
Hey.

16:58.810 --> 16:59.643
You all right?

17:05.022 --> 17:06.222
(booming)

17:06.222 --> 17:09.323
(hisses) Are you hurt?

17:09.323 --> 17:10.156
Fuck.

17:20.475 --> 17:22.475
(gasps)

17:24.437 --> 17:27.336
(man breathes heavily)

17:27.336 --> 17:29.707
- I always wanted myself a black--

17:29.707 --> 17:32.096
(gun fires)
(yelps)

17:32.096 --> 17:33.790
(tense music)

17:33.790 --> 17:35.730
- [Man] Now you're next.

17:35.730 --> 17:38.940
Can't run from me!

17:38.940 --> 17:40.920
I see, no, I'm not there!

17:40.920 --> 17:42.439
Am I there?

17:42.439 --> 17:45.439
I'm everywhere!

17:47.001 --> 17:51.251
You can't hide from me, I see you!

17:52.268 --> 17:54.768
(man screams)

17:56.071 --> 17:56.904
You!

18:50.039 --> 18:52.539
(tense music)

18:59.602 --> 19:02.048
(metal clatters)

19:02.048 --> 19:06.631
(thudding)
(man yelps)

19:36.030 --> 19:39.447
(helicopter blades whir)

19:55.095 --> 19:58.428
(emergency sirens wail)

20:07.162 --> 20:08.820
- Nova, it's me!

20:08.820 --> 20:10.274
It's me, let me in!

20:10.274 --> 20:11.243
(knocking)
Nova!

20:12.290 --> 20:14.063
Need you to let me in, please!

20:15.170 --> 20:16.090
Now, now!

20:17.590 --> 20:19.040
I know you're afraid, please.

20:21.124 --> 20:21.957
Please.

20:22.900 --> 20:24.463
Please, please.

20:39.150 --> 20:41.180
- You all right, sister?

20:41.180 --> 20:42.600
- Yeah.

20:42.600 --> 20:44.323
Yeah, I'm all right.

20:54.030 --> 20:55.383
- Good.

20:55.383 --> 20:58.033
I saw that motherfucker
trying to go after you.

20:58.033 --> 21:00.263
But we ain't having
that today, not no more.

21:01.350 --> 21:03.193
We cleaning house today.

21:04.330 --> 21:06.230
Getting rid of all those white devils.

21:16.680 --> 21:18.143
You alone in here, sister?

21:21.130 --> 21:21.963
- Yeah.

21:22.960 --> 21:23.923
This is my studio.

21:24.800 --> 21:27.620
You read a lot, that's good.

21:27.620 --> 21:30.670
We need smart black women
to raise our children.

21:30.670 --> 21:32.120
The white devils have been poisoning them

21:32.120 --> 21:33.113
with lies about us.

21:52.725 --> 21:56.045
(guns fire)
(emergency sirens wail)

21:56.045 --> 21:57.376
- Yo, Adisa!

21:57.376 --> 21:58.810
Yo, man.

21:58.810 --> 22:00.913
Yo, dog, come on, man.

22:02.550 --> 22:04.590
They coming, man, come on, bro.

22:04.590 --> 22:05.423
They coming!

22:15.160 --> 22:16.310
- Come with us, sister.

22:17.410 --> 22:20.063
We ain't free yet, there's a
lot of fighting to be done.

22:21.080 --> 22:21.913
- No.

22:22.796 --> 22:23.796
I'm gonna stay here.

22:24.700 --> 22:26.120
- Yo, man!

22:26.120 --> 22:26.953
Come on!

22:39.770 --> 22:41.660
- You can breathe now.

22:41.660 --> 22:42.493
They're gone.

22:45.200 --> 22:46.033
- I'm sorry.

22:47.790 --> 22:49.440
I don't know what happened to me.

22:50.540 --> 22:51.860
I froze.

22:51.860 --> 22:52.693
- Forget it.

22:57.110 --> 22:58.890
- What about the little girl?

22:58.890 --> 23:00.993
- It wasn't real, it was a doll.

23:03.480 --> 23:04.313
- A doll?

23:05.440 --> 23:06.980
- Forget it.

23:06.980 --> 23:08.880
We've got other things to worry about.

23:11.260 --> 23:12.510
It's gonna get dark soon.

23:13.650 --> 23:16.200
And things are probably
only gonna get a lot worse.

23:17.140 --> 23:17.973
Come on.

23:20.045 --> 23:22.795
(dramatic music)

23:55.819 --> 23:59.078
(people shout)

23:59.078 --> 24:02.161
(electricity buzzes)

24:05.480 --> 24:06.313
Oh great.

24:08.280 --> 24:09.930
Somebody must have cut the lines.

24:11.633 --> 24:13.108
(phone rings)

24:13.108 --> 24:14.747
(ominous music)

24:14.747 --> 24:17.230
I thought you said...

24:17.230 --> 24:18.530
- They must have fixed it.

24:26.438 --> 24:29.889
- [Lestor] Nova. (chatters)

24:29.889 --> 24:30.972
- Yes, but...

24:33.445 --> 24:35.190
It's not a problem, she's...

24:38.237 --> 24:39.070
Okay.

24:40.699 --> 24:41.532
Okay.

24:43.230 --> 24:44.280
I'll do what you say.

24:52.340 --> 24:55.390
Good news, friends are all right.

24:55.390 --> 24:56.940
Just taking longer to get here.

25:22.598 --> 25:24.674
- Pick up, pick up.

25:24.674 --> 25:26.946
(dial tone blares)

25:26.946 --> 25:27.779
Damn.

25:33.023 --> 25:34.795
What do we do now?

25:34.795 --> 25:37.462
(ominous music)

25:49.437 --> 25:52.687
(serene country music)

26:04.375 --> 26:05.486
- You're kidding.

26:07.710 --> 26:08.543
- Oh my god.

26:29.313 --> 26:31.390
- I don't feel like drinking.

26:31.390 --> 26:32.333
- Oh, come on.

26:33.240 --> 26:35.390
It's the end of everything
we know outside.

26:36.320 --> 26:38.320
You and I should both be dead right now.

26:43.530 --> 26:45.030
That's at least worth a drink.

26:47.560 --> 26:48.660
- Okay, fine.

26:48.660 --> 26:50.360
Give me it, you talked me into it.

26:54.510 --> 26:55.343
- Cheers.

26:56.410 --> 26:57.243
- Cheers.

27:12.424 --> 27:13.970
- [Nova] You got somewhere to be?

27:13.970 --> 27:14.803
- Yes.

27:16.020 --> 27:16.970
No, I...

27:19.770 --> 27:21.320
I was going to visit my father.

27:22.350 --> 27:23.450
He gave me this watch.

27:28.060 --> 27:30.673
I was going to visit his
grave to tell him something.

27:32.750 --> 27:33.800
- Your father's dead?

27:35.964 --> 27:37.590
- Yeah.

27:37.590 --> 27:38.423
Three years now.

27:41.730 --> 27:44.133
When he gave me this watch, he said,

27:46.407 --> 27:49.487
"There's always time
to do the right thing."

27:52.160 --> 27:54.360
I try to remember that
when times get tough.

27:56.956 --> 27:58.756
- What were you gonna tell your dad?

28:00.180 --> 28:01.013
- What?

28:02.000 --> 28:03.790
- You said that you were
on the way to the cemetery

28:03.790 --> 28:05.290
to tell your father something.

28:06.410 --> 28:07.243
What was it?

28:11.230 --> 28:13.230
- You don't seem worried about all this.

28:14.130 --> 28:17.753
I mean, it's like you said,
it is the end of the world.

28:18.920 --> 28:19.943
Don't you care?

28:20.990 --> 28:21.853
- I care.

28:23.280 --> 28:25.130
There'll be something after all this.

28:29.591 --> 28:32.270
- Is that what it says
in "The White Wave"?

28:32.270 --> 28:33.820
- [Nova] What?

28:33.820 --> 28:36.633
- The book on the table.

28:38.890 --> 28:40.690
- It's just a book a friend gave me.

28:41.700 --> 28:43.393
I know a lot of crazy people.

28:45.910 --> 28:50.043
Lestor, he's got a lot of
crazy ideas about the world.

28:51.350 --> 28:53.480
- This the same friend that's on the way?

28:53.480 --> 28:55.160
- [Nova] Who, Lestor?

28:55.160 --> 28:56.390
Yeah.

28:56.390 --> 28:57.463
Him and some others.

28:59.290 --> 29:01.713
- Some others with crazy ideas?

29:02.570 --> 29:04.380
- You ask a lot of questions.

29:04.380 --> 29:05.273
You a cop?

29:17.100 --> 29:18.400
- [Fay] What's in the van?

29:19.500 --> 29:22.083
- I don't know, cleaning supplies?

29:23.140 --> 29:24.423
It belongs to Lestor.

29:25.460 --> 29:28.153
That's why he's coming, to pick it up.

29:30.610 --> 29:32.550
- Must be something pretty important

29:32.550 --> 29:34.707
to drive through a war to pick up a van.

29:43.514 --> 29:45.375
(heart thumps)

29:45.375 --> 29:47.875
(tense music)

29:49.404 --> 29:52.071
- You should've never came here.

30:03.916 --> 30:07.499
- What's in the van, Nova?

30:11.085 --> 30:13.585
You put something in my drink?

30:18.655 --> 30:19.488
Why?

30:24.773 --> 30:25.606
Why?

30:29.095 --> 30:29.928
Why?

30:31.546 --> 30:33.629
Why, why did you do this?

30:52.567 --> 30:55.484
(foreboding music)

31:20.024 --> 31:21.691
- What have we here?

31:23.465 --> 31:25.882
She's still breathing.

31:30.757 --> 31:31.590
Love.

31:36.026 --> 31:36.943
Well, shit.

31:38.168 --> 31:40.800
- Man, stay out of it--

31:40.800 --> 31:42.480
- Come on, man, this is the time--

31:42.480 --> 31:44.129
- Don't you fucking touch--

31:44.129 --> 31:46.580
- Whoa, what is your problem, man?

31:46.580 --> 31:49.830
Don't fucking touch me, don't touch me.

31:50.801 --> 31:55.358
- You find some rope, I
want you to guys tie her up,

31:55.358 --> 31:56.918
set her off to the side,

31:56.918 --> 31:58.870
we'll figure out what
to do with her later.

31:58.870 --> 32:01.700
Right now we gotta get our shit together,

32:01.700 --> 32:04.678
cause we got somewhere to be, don't we?

32:04.678 --> 32:06.340
- Go grab the rope, man.

32:06.340 --> 32:08.944
He told you to get the rope, dumb.

32:08.944 --> 32:12.027
(slow motion speech)

32:17.436 --> 32:20.103
(ominous music)

32:23.754 --> 32:25.754
(gasps)

32:43.935 --> 32:46.980
(sighs)
- Baby?

32:46.980 --> 32:48.430
What's wrong, couldn't sleep?

32:50.140 --> 32:51.943
Must've been thinking about me, huh?

32:51.943 --> 32:53.893
- (giggles) Shut up.

32:56.310 --> 32:57.350
No, I...

32:58.520 --> 33:01.003
I just had the craziest dream.

33:03.525 --> 33:04.873
I can't even remember.

33:08.240 --> 33:09.323
I was alone,

33:11.530 --> 33:15.263
and I kept calling you,
but you weren't there.

33:16.575 --> 33:17.575
- Well I'm here now.

33:18.510 --> 33:20.527
What was it that you wanted?

33:21.634 --> 33:22.775
- What?

33:22.775 --> 33:25.030
- In your dream, you
said you were calling me.

33:25.030 --> 33:26.080
All right, here I am.

33:27.080 --> 33:27.913
What'd you want?

33:30.040 --> 33:31.890
- I...

33:31.890 --> 33:33.113
I can't remember.

33:40.840 --> 33:41.753
- I got an idea.

